                <p>This <expan>indentur<ex>e</ex></expan> maed the last day of January in the 
                xxiij<hi rend="superscript">to</hi> yere of the reigne of Kyng Harry the 
                Viij<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> bitwene the Right Honorable Sir Thomas West
                Knyght Lorde Lawarr of the one <expan>p<ex>ar</ex>tie</expan> And Roberte Thorne 
                Citzen <lb/> <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr><expan>and</expan></choice> 
                <expan>m<ex>er</ex>chu<ex>a</ex>nt</expan> of London on the other 
                <expan>p<ex>ar</ex>tie</expan>. Witnessithe that it is <expan>coven<ex>a</ex>ntid</expan>
                <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr><expan>and</expan></choice> agreid bitwene the said 
                <expan>p<ex>ar</ex>ties</expan> in <expan>man<ex>er</ex></expan> 
                <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr><expan>and</expan></choice> forme folowing. That is to say the
                seyde <expan>Rob<ex>er</ex>t</expan> Thorne <expan>coven<ex>a</ex>ntith</expan>
                <expan>gr<ex>a</ex>ntith</expan> <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr><expan>and</expan></choice>
                agreethe to <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr><expan>and</expan></choice>
                <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></abbr><expan>w<ex>ith</ex></expan></choice> 
                the sayd <lb/> Lord Lawarr that if a sure sufficient
                <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr><expan>and</expan></choice> ?indesciable estate in fee
                simple be made or causid to be maed ?or conveyed by the sayd Lorde Lawarr 
                <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr><expan>and</expan></choice> one George Croft 
                <expan>mast<ex>er</ex></expan> of the house <choice><abbr>&amp;</abbr>
                <expan>and</expan></choice> hospitall of Seint Bartilinaws in
